## Naming Conventions

### Java
- **Classes:** PascalCase (`UserService`, `CreditServiceImpl`)
- **Interfaces:** PascalCase, no `I` prefix (`CreditService`, `PaymentService`)
- **Methods/Variables:** camelCase, verb-noun (`fetchUser`, `validateInput`)
- **Constants:** UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (`HEADER_TENANT_ID`)
- **Packages:** lowercase, domain-grouped (`credit.service`, `signup.pipeline`)
- **DTOs:** Suffix with `Dto` | **Entities:** No suffix | **Repos:** Suffix `Repository` | **Controllers:** Suffix `Controller`
- **Test files:** `<Class>Test.java`

### Angular / TypeScript
- **Components:** kebab-case selectors, PascalCase classes
- **Services:** `.service.ts` suffix | **Interceptors:** `.interceptor.ts` | **Guards:** `.guard.ts`
- **Feature folders:** `src/app/features/<domain>/` | **Core:** `src/app/core/services/`

### Terraform
- **Modules:** kebab-case folders | **Resources:** snake_case | **Variables:** snake_case

### Database
- **Tables:** snake_case, plural | **Columns:** snake_case | **Migrations:** `V<N>__<Description>.sql`

---

## Component / Utility Reuse Catalogue

### Shared Modules (reach for these FIRST)
- `common-dto` → `TenantContext`, `HeaderNames`, `ErrorCodes`, `TenantConstants`
- `common-infra` → `TenantFilter`, `TenantAuditingListener`, `CacheService`, `DistributedLockService`, `ApiRateLimiter`, `HttpClientFactory`, `JsonResponseWriter`

### Auth Service
- Signup pipeline: `SignupAction` → `SignupPipeline`
- Credit system: `CreditService` (grant, consume, validate)
- Referral system: `ReferralService`
- Email: `EmailService` → `SesEmailService` (prod) / `DevEmailService` (local)
- Admin: `AuthorizationService`, `AuthorizationAspect`, `AdminUserService`, `AdminCreditService`

### Backend Service
- Ledger: `LedgerParser` → `LedgerExcelParser`
- Export: `ExportStrategy` → `Rule37ExcelExportStrategy`
- Credit consumption: `CreditClient` (WebClient)

### Frontend
- `auth.service.ts`, `http-client.service.ts`, `base-api.service.ts`, `admin-api.service.ts`
- Guards: `authGuard`, `guestGuard`, `adminGuard`

